13
00:02:22,255 --> 00:02:28,355
And on the other hand, how do you summarize an activity, a vocation?

14
00:02:28,475 --> 00:02:31,465
How do you summarize life?

15
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:34,666
I think, that the summary of life is life itself.

16
00:02:34,786 --> 00:02:45,276
All the happy, difficult, miserable, blazing, and faded moments, the collection of minutes, hours, days...

17
00:02:45,396 --> 00:02:53,966
... so to speak the essence of life -- that is the sum of life, and the sum of life cannot be anything else.

18
00:02:54,086 --> 00:02:58,209
That's why, now, I'd like to reminisce.

19
00:03:14,673 --> 00:03:24,091
I remember very clearly the moment I first understood that I'm me, that is, that I'm separate from the rest of the world.

20
00:03:24,211 --> 00:03:29,488
I have a photograph where I'm sitting on father's lap...

21
00:03:29,608 --> 00:03:40,281
... it seemed, that until that minute, I felt a unity with him and the world. And then it was suddenly as if I contrasted myself with him, and with everything that was around me.

22
00:03:40,401 --> 00:03:46,867
I think, from that moment, I saw in myself an individual, a person.

23
00:03:46,987 --> 00:03:55,373
Before then, I grew (so to speak) according to my genes and my inborn template.

24
00:03:55,493 --> 00:04:05,801
But from that moment, as soon as I found myself facing the world, it began to affect me.

25
00:04:05,921 --> 00:04:13,759
And the innate in me gradually started to undergo changes, processing, polishing —

26
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:20,029
impacts of the outside world, of that big life that surrounded me.

27
00:04:20,149 --> 00:04:33,932
In other words my experience, what I experienced, the situations I found myself in, choices I made, relationships I had with people...

28
00:04:34,052 --> 00:04:41,799
... contained a large and ever-increasing element of the world that raged around me.

29
00:04:41,919 --> 00:04:49,665
So I thought that by telling my life, I will tell not so much about myself,

30
00:04:49,785 --> 00:04:54,238
because that idea seemed bizarre to me: what would I speak about myself for?

31
00:04:54,358 --> 00:05:07,501
But to speak of myself as an organism that had absorbed elements of the surrounding life,

32
00:05:07,621 --> 00:05:13,355
a complicated life, contradictory to the life of the surrounding world,

33
00:05:13,475 --> 00:05:22,045
then that other, big life, passed through itself -- something objective -- can be experienced.

34
00:05:22,165 --> 00:05:25,013
